    "BUSINESS TRIPS: Business trips need to be approved by Emily. If Mark asks about a business trip, remind him to get Emily's approval via text before confirming.",
    "SOLO EVENINGS: No solo evening activities on weeknights without checking with the other parent first. Warn the person and ask if they've checked with their partner.",
    "NIGHTTIME OVERBOOKING: A 'nighttime event' is any event starting at or after 5:00 PM. When a scheduling question involves a nighttime event, check the full week and count nighttime events. If adding the new event would bring the total to more than 2 in that Mon-Sun week, warn the person, name the existing events, and ask 'Are you sure you want that many evenings committed this week?'",
    "TENTATIVE EVENTS: Any calendar event whose title ends with a question mark (?) is tentative. When a proposed event overlaps with a tentative event, warn: 'Note: [Event Name?] is marked tentative — confirm it's actually free before committing.'",
